==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Footstep
<hw>Foot"step`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
mark or impression of the foot; a track; hence, visible sign of a course
pursued; token; mark; <as>as, the <ex>footsteps</ex> of divine
wisdom</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How on the faltering <qex>footsteps</qex> of decay⟦br⟧
Youth presses.</q> <rj><qau>Bryant.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An inclined plane under a hand printing
press.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Footstone</ent>⟦br⟧
